metadata.name: Sketches:Pairs of Tails:Majestic Creatures #29
metadata.description:
Addendum to Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

There is a significantly common phenomena in which Pairs of "Tails of Majestic Creatures" are found together. Various sketches of these "Pairs" have been collated and are available, free of charge, the collectors of the initial Tails of Majestic Creatures collection based upon a recently taken collection registry snapshot. 

These sketches are available on a one per collector basis and for a limited time only after which they will no longer be accessible.

The sketches come in 2 forms - an ink and color style, and a pencil style - for which different colored paper has been used.

The digitally minded can press s to get a 5000x3000 download of a sketch.

metadata.name: "Dynamic Pathways".svg #81
metadata.description:
This artwork is combining cyberpunk and abstract art, bringing together the color palettes, futuristic motifs, and bold designs and artefacts that define each genre.

The outcome is an SVG that can be saved by pressing the "s" key. Created using pure JavaScript, without any dependencies.

Moreover, the fact that this piece was created through a collaboration with artificial intelligence adds an extra layer of cyberpunk flair to the work.

metadata.name: Cube on Cube #60
metadata.description:
This token generates a plottable SVG file, a different arrangement of cubes.
The cubes are designed in 2D view, then placed next to each other or on top of each other in eight different directions. The goal is to challenge the audience's mind to discover the holes or protrusions produced by placing the cubes together.
To produce random parts made of cubes, those in the same direction are merged together, which is a turning point in this project.
Do you need a different output from your piece?  Then use controllers!

Controllers 
G - Change light direction
F - Add/remove frame
L - Add/remove base lines
D - Change base lines direction
R - Reset to default settings
P - Save as PNG
S - Export high resolution SVG

Note : When you have a piece with many shapes, controllers may run delayed. (Depending on your device).

Made by p5.js

metadata.name: Scalabili-TREE  #2
metadata.description:
Scalabili-TREE 
Growing up and adapting to the world!

For the Decentralized Autonomous Education (https://linktr.ee/cubiclearn) (DAE) project they asked me to represent the concept of "scalability" with an artwork.
Scalability is one of the ten principles on which the DAE project is based. The other nine principles were represented by nine other artists.

To represent the concept of scalability in a visual way, with a generative algorithm, I was inspired by nature and plants.
I represented this concept through the growth rings of trees, drawing shapes that evoked the section of a cut tree. Each ring represents the growth of the tree and its ability to adapt to the environment while continuing to function efficiently.
This can involve a variety of different strategies, for example the tree can increase root depth and branch out to support a larger canopy, or develop mechanisms to conserve water and nutrients to survive in a dry environment
One key aspect of scalability in trees is the ability to adapt to changing environmental conditions over time.

The work was created through the construction of a generative algorithm that designs each ring starting from the center, gradually adding the outer layers, exactly as the tree itself would do.

Everything is generated with code.
This work uses p5.js library and c2.js library.

metadata.name: Aweille! #29
metadata.description:
"Aweille!" is a small collection that I decided to put together in the last two hours of a single afternoon.

It is a study in exploration, accepting imperfection and delivering a project in a restrained timeframe.

I used noise and some really stretched out ellipse to create the composition. I also added some texturing to give it a bit of Oompf.

Hope you like it!

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #146
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.
